        "title": "fix(tts): strip reasoning content from summarization output",
        "body": "fix(tts): strip reasoning content from summarization output\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nTTS summarization output includes verbose reasoning/thinking content that should be stripped before being spoken aloud. Users hear long chains of reasoning instead of the actual answer.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nStrip reasoning content from TTS summarization output so only the actual response text is spoken.\n\nFixes #90364.\n\n## Evidence\n\nTargeted test:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/tts/tts-core.test.ts\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  4 passed (4)\n  Duration  23.27s\n```\n\nFormatting:\n\n```text\n$ npx oxfmt --check src/tts/tts-core.ts src/tts/tts-core.test.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\nWhitespace:\n\n```text\n$ git diff --check\n```",
